Here’s a **clear, exam-ready difference between CPM and PERT** 👇

---

## ✅ CPM vs PERT (Core Idea)

* **CPM (Critical Path Method)** → used when time is **fixed / known**
* **PERT (Program Evaluation Review Technique)** → used when time is **uncertain**

---

## ✅ Key Differences

| Basis               | CPM                         | PERT                                                  |
| ------------------- | --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Full Form           | Critical Path Method        | Program Evaluation Review Technique                   |
| Nature              | Deterministic (fixed time)  | Probabilistic (uncertain time)                        |
| Time Estimate       | Single time value           | Three estimates: optimistic, most likely, pessimistic |
| Focus               | Time + Cost optimization    | Time (uncertainty handling)                           |
| Type of Projects    | Construction, manufacturing | Research, development, new projects                   |
| Complexity          | Simple                      | More complex                                          |
| Probability Concept | Not used                    | Used                                                  |
| Critical Path       | Fixed                       | May vary (based on estimates)                         |

---

## ✅ Important Formula (PERT only)

T_e = \frac{O + 4M + P}{6}

Where:

* **O** = Optimistic time
* **M** = Most likely time
* **P** = Pessimistic time

---

## ✅ One-Line Difference (for quick writing)

👉 **CPM = fixed time planning**
👉 **PERT = uncertain time estimation using probability**

